===Determiner===
{{en-det}}

# Each of the two; one and the [[other]]; {{non-gloss definition|referring to two individuals or items}}.
#: {{ux|en|'''Both''' children are such dolls.}}
#*{{RQ:KJV|Genesis|21|27||Abraham took sheep and oxen, and gave them unto Abimelech; and '''both''' of them made a covenant.}}
#* '''1717''', {{w|Henry St John, 1st Viscount Bolingbroke|Viscount Bolingbroke}}, ''Reflexions upon Exile''
#*: He will not bear the loss of his rank, because he can bear the loss of his estate; but he will bear '''both''', because he is prepared for both.

====Usage notes====
This word does not come between a possessive and its head noun.  Say ''both of my hands'' or ''both my hands'',  not *''my both hands''.  Say, ''both the king's horses'', not *''the king's both horses''.

